    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the tomato sauce is cooking, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until softened</p><p>Whilst the onion is cooking, add your <strong>dried</strong> <strong>yeast</strong> to a large bowl with 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml] </span><strong>warm</strong> <strong>water</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong>, give it a good mix up and set aside for 5-10 min for the yeast to develop</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1678802271998-x200.jpg",
