            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>mushrooms</strong> to the pan and cook for 2-3 min further, then add your <strong>spinach</strong> and cook for a final 1-2 min or until wilted – this is your <strong>stromboli</strong> <strong>filling</strong></p><p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>pizza</strong> <strong>base</strong> <strong>mix</strong> to the bowl with the yeast</p><p>Gradually add up to 60ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[90ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[120ml]</span> <strong>warm</strong> <strong>water</strong> (you may not need all of it), a little at a time, and gently mix with a plastic spatula until a sticky dough ball has formed</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1678802275788-x200.jpg",
